<br>
Even so, it's pretty weak to say &quot;SHOW THE PROOF it was intentional&quot;.  Intent is within a person's mind, and there is no proof of intent, per se.  Instead, there is proof of actions, from which you have to infer intent.  As I said, Arch has made a pretty believable case so far, but the other side of the story does have enough details to enable you to infer intent, if you happened to believe that side of the story over Arch's.  <br>
<br>
If you want absolute proof of intent, short of an admission, you're never going to get it.  But you don't need it.  In our legal system, if intent is an element of a crime, you can prove intent by inference from the person's actions.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fuhglywuhgly>Fuhgly Wuhgly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/15/03 6:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3303.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WATCH out for an idiot named ARCH</span><hr size=1> I don't understand how a fucking 65 SK with years exp can fucking train anyone on accident.<br>
